CHANGELOG — Do It List

Plain text. Append-only. Chronological (oldest first). Records scope, requirement, and doc-structure changes — not git commit history.
Keep entries CONCISE: one line, the what + a brief why. No implementation detail (that lives in commits/code). Aim ≤ ~200 chars.
Prior history (2026-05-05 … 2026-06-15) is in CHANGELOG.archive.log.

2026-06-15  Rotated the changelog: full prior history → CHANGELOG.archive.log; adopted a one-line, concise entry style (entries had grown into paragraphs).
2026-06-15  Arc 5 O&C +item 18: make co-assignee add/remove/reorder optimistic (round-trips today, feels sluggish; UX_GUARDRAILS §6).
2026-06-15  Arc 5 O&C: swapped items 17/18 (optimistic co-assignee now 17, Viewer+ now 18 — done last per sequence); tightened the Viewer+ wording.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 O&C item 18 (Viewer+) reworked: grant is direct-assignee-only (not co); a viewer+ leads its subtree (progress/comments) and may assign descendants only to that task's existing co's — no team expansion.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 O&C item 18 (Viewer+): a viewer+ lead can staff descendants with primary AND co-assignees, but only from a fixed pool (their led task's co's) — pool only shrinks down-tree, so no team expansion.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 O&C item 18 (Viewer+) restructured into action subitems 18.1-18.6 (setting/seed, direct grant, descendant staffing, pool-limited dropdowns, label, tests); invariant rationale stays prose on the parent. Convention upheld, not relaxed.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 O&C: item 17 broken into subitems 17.1-17.3 (add/remove/reorder, reconcile/revert as parent prose); dropped the "do 13 first" override — remaining work runs lowest-first (layout 1-12, then 17, 18).
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 14 (Testing) fleshed out: 7 subitems — one in-browser pass per surface (resize sweep, rail, people pane, flyout, optimistic co's, viewer+) + a full mix-test gate; per-item unit suites are the automated coverage.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 Open Questions pruned to the two real ones (breakpoint value, reframed around column-fit; people-pane naming). Resolved into item specs: description wrap = two-line clamp (item 3), people-pane empty = render nothing (item 9), add default role = viewer (items 10/11); dropped the "decide at impl" drop-feedback non-question.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 Open Questions section removed (both closed): breakpoint sizing folded into item 5 (~1800–2000 px, three-columns-fit, not monitor class); people pane named "Collaborators" (item 9).
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 4 (index card-grid expansion) removed — the index is now a deliberate single-column drag-to-reorder list and a 2D grid would break the vertical reorder. Items renumbered (old 5–14 → 4–13).
2026-06-15  Co-avatar cap bumped 3 → 8 (item 15's pre-scoped post-testing step); chip now stacks up to 8 co-assignee avatars before "+N".
2026-06-15  Arc 5 items 4–7: custom 3xl breakpoint (~1800px) + ultrawide triple-pane — left rail (Initiatives index, in Layouts chrome) with role badge + mini progress, current highlighted, click-current-closes.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 6: index at 3xl is a real triple-pane — center keeps the "pick an Initiative" prompt, the right (third) pane holds the "Assigned to Me" placeholder (Arc 7 fills it). Cross-arc pointer in m02.07 item 1; fixed stale m02.07 ref (co-assignees is m02.05 item 12, not 13).
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 8: Collaborators pane in the left rail — Initiatives.list_collaborators/1 (one query: initiatives→members→users), deduped, most-shared-first, avatar + name + shared count; renders nothing when you share with no one.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 8 refinements: pane titled "My Collaborators"; avatars carry a global online dot (new app-wide presence topic tracked from the authed on_mount — lit when connected anywhere, not just in a shared Initiative).
2026-06-15  Arc 5 items 9–10: add/remove a collaborator to/from an Initiative — click opens a contextual menu (add as viewer / remove via the existing hand-off flow), and drag a collaborator onto a rail entry to add them there. Both route through Initiatives.add_collaborator_as_viewer/3 (owner-only, no-op if already a member).
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 11: narrow-screen flyout for the left rail — below 3xl, an open Initiative shows a left-edge tab that slides the rail in as an overlay (client-only toggle); absent on the plain index. Layout phase (items 1–11) complete.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 fix: item 11's flyout collapsed the ultrawide grid at 3xl — `not-data-open:hidden` (0-2-0) outranked plain `3xl:block` (0-1-0), hiding the left rail so the center fell into the rail track and A2M ballooned. Fixed with `3xl:not-data-open:block` (mirrors the right rail).
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 12.5: optimistic co-assignees — a CoAssignees hook applies add/remove/reorder to the Details pane (and mirrors the row-chip avatar stack) at the gesture, deferred a microtask so LiveView reads phx-values first; the existing server events reconcile and revert. Chip co-stack now always-rendered (hidden when empty) so it can sync from zero.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 12.6.1: Viewer+ setting + seed — initiatives.viewer_plus (default on) cast in the changeset, seeded from a new My-Initiative-Defaults pref (initiative_viewer_plus); owner-only per-initiative toggle in the Details Settings + the account default. Permission grant comes next (12.6.2+).
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 12.5 fix: optimistic co-assignee remove/reorder broke after one use — the pane `<li>`s had no stable id, so morphdom matched by position and mangled the list on the server patch (detaching phx-click bindings → events never reached the server, DB unchanged). Added `id="co-row-<uid>"` so reconciliation matches by key.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 12.5 REVERTED: the optimistic co-assignee layer (CoAssignees hook + markers) masked server failures — it showed add/remove/reorder as done even when the write never landed, and the stable-id fix didn't cure it. Ripped it out; co-assignees are an honest server round-trip again (12.5 reopened, to be redone without the lying-UI failure mode).
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 12.5 redo (can't-lie): optimistic co-assignees rebuilt — the pane list is hook-owned (keyed <ul> + phx-update=ignore, no morphdom fight); each add/remove/reorder snapshots the list, applies it, then pushes the event WITH A REPLY and reverts the snapshot on {ok:false} or an 8s timeout. with_co now replies {ok:bool}. A write that doesn't land snaps back instead of sticking. (Pending browser re-test.)
